ady rhythm and the lattice stills around your steps, granting you an aisle of truce through the crawl. Two market scribes above, who hear the sanctioned chime, later testify that they witnessed you enter in rite and depart with a sealed bundle, and that written witness will harden your evidence when the Charter calls you to account. But authority draws eyes, and a River Lords tally-scribe lurking near the western rail notes your presence and sends a neat report to Ulo Hen, who will try to spin it as collusion unless you frame the story first. You retrieve the seals, the Saltlick scrap, and Kessa Tharn’s memo without scrape or stumble, and the memo’s wax takes your oath-mark clean, which makes it more difficult to dismiss. Thia grits her teeth at the attention but, seeing your care with her people, gives you the full lantern-signal phrase that traces a safe path toward the Saltlick Terraces when the wind is in the east.\"},\n        {\"id\": \"C3-3\", \"title\": \"Confront a Rafter Night-Sentry\", \"text\": \"You catch the flicker of a watch coal and choose to face it instead of creeping past, because sometimes the straight walk leaves fewer knives at your back. A Rafter Guild sentry crouches in a cutout, knuckles scarred and eyes rimmed red from nights on the cables, and he startles when your lantern finds his badge. You speak first with respect for the work that holds the city aloft, and you do not hide the seals or the ledger scrap when he asks what brings a Breathkeeper paladin under the market at this hour. You show him the knot-work and ask him, as a craftsman, what he sees when he looks at the bites and turns, and you watch the moment pride wrestles with fear behind his teeth. You do not accuse, you listen, and in that listening you offer him a way to be larger than the rumor that would make him a thug.\", \"outcome\": \"The sentry swallows hard and admits, in five slow sentences each weighed like stones, that the knots were taught by a foreman whose temper ha